President Biden announced that his administration has achieved its goal of administering 100 million COVID-19 vaccine shots in the first 100 days in office, ahead of schedule. He highlighted the progress made in vaccinating vulnerable populations, particularly seniors, and emphasized the efforts taken to increase vaccine supply, establish vaccination sites, and ensure equity in distribution. President Biden also mentioned the importance of the American Rescue Plan in supporting vaccination efforts and reopening schools safely. He urged Americans to continue following safety protocols and get vaccinated when eligible, emphasizing the need for herd immunity to stop wearing masks. President Biden expressed optimism for a more normal Fourth of July celebration but cautioned that there is still a long way to go in fighting the pandemic.